steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6l13o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ar2s4","text":"Using the small (1 µl) end of a sterile Combi Loop, generously streak P. fluorescens SBW25 from a glycerol stock onto LB agar plates and incubate overnight at T","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":70,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":159,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"38lst","text":"Aim to streak out cells so that nearly confluent growth is obtained (i.e. NOT single, isolated colonies).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7gh01","text":"Prepare one streak plate for each transformation that you plan to do.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"duuif","text":"Use antibiotic-free LB agar plates for WT cells","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2j0s8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3c3kf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"9E7C1B9039DE11ED8827838C9DB6C234","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"30","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fr74t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3jtn1","text":"For each plate, use the large (10 µl) end of a sterile Combi Loop to gently scrape the cells from the plate and transfer to a sterile, 2.0 mL microcentrifuge tube containing 1 mL sterile 15% glycerol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6fhep","text":"Cells can be picked up efficiently by starting at the top of the plate and running the loop back and forth over the surface.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bd1q5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"48glt","text":"Resuspend the cells by gentle vortexing, and pellet by centrifuging at 10,000 rpm for 1 minute (increase speed/time if supernatant remains cloudy).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9dv7d","text":"Remove the supernatant by pipetting, avoiding the cell pellet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1bt9a","text":"Wash the pellet three more times with 1 mL 15% glycerol.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9b2k4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8l4cg","text":"Resuspend the final pellet in 100 ul 15% glycerol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ftthi","text":"Each pellet provides one transformation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3fk75","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fr3ik","text":"Label and chill electroporation cuvettes on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1knsq","text":"Dilute DNA to be electroporated to a final volume of 5 ul.  Add to cell suspension and flick gently to mix.  Place DNA/cell mixture on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2r4cb","text":"To avoid arcing, it is important to keep the salt concentration of DNA preps as low as possible. DNA preps should be eluted with nuclease-free water. All DNA dilutions should be made with nuclease-free water.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3j49t","text":"For replicative plasmids use 10 - 50 ng DNA.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"18gco","text":"Use 500 ng DNA for nonreplicative plasmids.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5jfah","text":"IMPORTANT CONTROL:  always prepare one negative control with cells + water only to check for background colonies and stability of antibiotic on the plate.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jbni","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
